data.title: Press-Telegram Girls Track and Field Dream Team: Wilson’s Loren Webster is athlete of the year
data.meta_description: See the Press-Telegram's 2024 selections for the girls track and field Dream Team across all of the events, including the selections for athlete and coach of the year.
data.text:
PRESS-TELEGRAM GIRLS TRACK AND FIELD DREAM TEAM 2024

ATHLETE OF THE YEAR

Loren Webster, Wilson

Wilson junior Loren Webster has been selected as the Press-Telegram Girls Track and Field Athlete of the Year after winning the state title in the long jump on May 25.

Webster jumped 20 feet and 5¼ inches at the CIF state championships, securing her first individual state title by nearly one foot over the second-place finisher. The 10 points she earned were pivotal in Wilson’s ability to win back-to-back state titles.

Webster also finished first in the Moore League Finals (20-9.50 PR) and CIF Southern Section Division 1 Finals (19-7.50),

“Hopefully, 22 (feet) next year. Look out for that,” Webster said after her win at the state meet in Clovis.

Webster also anchored Wilson’s 4×100 relay team to a sixth-place finish at the state meet in 46.64, which gave the Bruins three key points in the team standings.

COACH OF THE YEAR

Neil Nelson, Wilson

Wilson track coach Neil Nelson led the Bruins to back-to-back CIF State championships for the first time in program history.

Nelson believes a three-peat is possible next year. His team returns several top athletes who scored individually at the state meet, including juniors Loren Webster and Kaylin Edwards, sophomore Brooke Blue and freshman Saniah Varnado. The Bruins, who won the state title in the 4×400 relay, are also expected to be competitive in the 4×100 and 4×800 relays.

“I know we have to put the hard work in. I know we have to get back and we have to grind, but we know how hard it was this year so we’re going to grind even harder to get it back (next year),” Nelson said after winning a second straight CIF title.

Wilson scored 36 points to defeat runner-up Ventura (30 points) at Buchanan High on May 25.
